Butterworth police say the accused allegedly dragged the 16-year-old to her room where she was attacked. CAPE TOWN - A 20-year-old man has been sentenced to ten years behind bars for raping a family member. Butterworth police say the accused allegedly dragged the 16-year-old to her room where she was attacked. Here’s the police’s Jackson Manatha said: “We welcome the sentence but, unfortunately, we cannot identify the accused.”